*Description*

In Gradle 3+ the test results are in subdirectories defined by the name of the task that creates them, so the current default location for Gradle: {{./**/test-results/*.xml}} is not working. The change in Gradle is documented [here|https://docs.gradle.org/3.0/release-notes.html#unique-default-test-result-and-report-directories-for-test-tasks].

Instead we will need something like {{./**/test-results/**/*.xml}}. For example, the results would be placed in {{./**/test-results/test/*.xml}} because the test task is named &#x27;test&#x27;.

*Workaround*

The workaround is to specify the output directory in the Gradle configuration file:

{code}
#!groovy
test {
    reports.junitXml.destination = file("$buildDir/test-results")
}
{code}

For more details have a look to our docs [here|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucket/test-reporting-in-pipelines-939708543.html].

Unable to load past PR while scrolling down as browser console is showing the following error:

{code}
#!python
Failed to load resource: the server responded with a status of 500 (Internal Server Error)
{code}

The keyboard shortcut to submit a comment is currently {{CTRL+Enter}}, however on a Mac, the equivalent shortcut should be {{CMD+Enter}}.

In Bitbucket Server we detect the OS and use something like the following to figure out whether the event was one of the aforementioned shortcuts:

{code:js}
/* Return true if the ctrlKey is held down, or metaKey on Mac */
function isCtrlish(e) {
    return isMac ? e.metaKey : e.ctrlKey;
}

/* Return true if the ctrlKey is held down (or metaKey on Mac) as well as the enter key */
function isCtrlEnter(e) {
    return isCtrlish(e) && e.which === AJS.keyCode.ENTER;
}
{code}

Reproduction steps-

# Go to BitBucket.org
# Click on"?" icon and select "Keyboard shortcuts"

Expected - Help documentation is shown about the keyboard shortcuts\\
Actual- Error message in console

{code}
#!text

VM41:19 Uncaught TypeError: this.props.onKeyboardShortcutsActivated is not a function
{code}

Background - I was a regular user of the "dot menu" - I would press "." to bring up a search box to quickly get to my required repository. The "dot menu" is no longer working for me. As I was unsure if this was planned (as it coincides with some UI updates), I wanted to view the keyboard shortcuts help documentation, to confirm the best keyboard options for the new UI. Very frustrating to not be able to navigate purely from the keyboard at the moment...

Issuing a POST request to the BitBucket API to obtain an access token with the Client Credentials Grant flow results in an invalid request error due to missing callback URI:

{code}
#!json
{"error_description": "No callback uri defined for the OAuth client.", "error": "invalid_request"}
{code}

Command used to request access token as specified in the [documentation|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/bitbucket/oauth-2#4-client-credentials-grant-4-4]:

{code}
#!bash
curl -X POST -u "client_id:secret" https://bitbucket.org/site/oauth2/access_token -d grant_type=client_credential
{code}

The [Client Credentials Grant|https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749#section-4.4] flow does not require specifying a callback URI.

Workaround is to specify any callback URI in the OAuth consumers section of the account Settings->OAuth page.
